<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="525" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[841,911,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">aniso-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[960,1019,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">penis</emphasis>
, referring to the unequally lengthened distal process of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
